---

Why AGPL-3.0 for the code:

The methodology requires that operational components (the inference
harness, the translation pipeline, the sensor fleet) preserve specific
architectural invariants: no telemetry, sovereign substrate, open source.
AGPL-3.0 preserves these properties downstream — anyone who modifies a
component, including running a modified version as a network service,
must publish their modifications under the same license. This is the
structural defense against the invariants being silently broken by
closed-source forks operated as services.

A fork that needs a more permissive code license for legitimate reasons
may negotiate with Harmonia for a dual-licensing arrangement. The default
is AGPL-3.0; any departure from it is per-case.
